6173#if defined(__Userspace__)
6174 case AF_CONN:
6175 net->mtu += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
6176 break;
6177#endif
6178 default:
6179 break;
6180 }
6181 if (net->mtu < stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu) {
6182 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
6183 }
6184 }
6185 }
6186 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_PMTUD_ENABLE) {
6187 if (!SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->pmtu_timer.timer)) {
6188 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, inp, stcb, net);
6189 }
6190 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD;
6191 }
6192 if (paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt > 0) {
6193 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) {
6194 if (net->error_count > paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6195 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_PF;
6196 }
6197 } else {
6198 if ((net->error_count <= paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) &&
6199 (net->error_count > net->pf_threshold)) {
6200 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_PF;
6201 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6202 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT,
6203 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
6204 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_12);
6205 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
6206 }
6207 }
6208 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE) {
6209 if (net->error_count > paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6210 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
6211 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6212 }
6213 } else {
6214 if (net->error_count <= paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6215 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
6216 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6217 }
6218 }
6219 net->failure_threshold = paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt;
6220 }
6221 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_DSCP) {
6222 net->dscp = paddrp->spp_dscp & 0xfc;
6223 net->dscp |= 0x01;
6224 }
6225#ifdef INET6
6226 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_IPV6_FLOWLABEL) {
6227 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6228 net->flowlabel = paddrp->spp_ipv6_flowlabel & 0x000fffff;
6229 net->flowlabel |= 0x80000000;
6230 }
6231 }
6232#endif
6233 } else {
6234 /************************ASSOC ONLY -- NO NET SPECIFIC SET ******************/
6235 if (paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt > 0) {
6236 stcb->asoc.def_net_failure = paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt;
6237 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6238 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) {
6239 if (net->error_count > paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6240 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_PF;
6241 }
6242 } else {
6243 if ((net->error_count <= paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) &&
6244 (net->error_count > net->pf_threshold)) {
6245 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_PF;
6246 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6247 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT,
6248 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
6249 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_13);
6250 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
6251 }
6252 }
6253 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE) {
6254 if (net->error_count > paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6255 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
6256 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6257 }
6258 } else {
6259 if (net->error_count <= paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt) {
6260 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
6261 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6262 }
6263 }
6264 net->failure_threshold = paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt;
6265 }
6266 }
6267 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_ENABLE) {
6268 if (paddrp->spp_hbinterval != 0) {
6269 stcb->asoc.heart_beat_delay = paddrp->spp_hbinterval;
6270 } else if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_TIME_IS_ZERO) {
6271 stcb->asoc.heart_beat_delay = 0;
6272 }
6273 /* Turn back on the timer */
6274 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6275 if (paddrp->spp_hbinterval != 0) {
6276 net->heart_beat_delay = paddrp->spp_hbinterval;
6277 } else if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_TIME_IS_ZERO) {
6278 net->heart_beat_delay = 0;
6279 }
6280 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_NOHB) {
6281 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NOHB;
6282 }
6283 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, inp, stcb, net,
6284 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_14);
6285 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, inp, stcb, net);
6286 }
6287 sctp_stcb_feature_off(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONOT_HEARTBEAT);
6288 }
6289 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_DISABLE) {
6290 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6291 if (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_NOHB)) {
6292 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_NOHB;
6293 if (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED)) {
6294 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT,
6295 inp, stcb, net,
6296 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_15);
6297 }
6298 }
6299 }
6300 sctp_stcb_feature_on(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONOT_HEARTBEAT);
6301 }
6302 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_PMTUD_DISABLE) {
6303 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6304 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->pmtu_timer.timer)) {
6305 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, inp, stcb, net,
6306 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_16);
6307 }
6308 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD;
6309 if (paddrp->spp_pathmtu > 0) {
6310 net->mtu = paddrp->spp_pathmtu;
6311 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
6312#ifdef INET
6313 case AF_INET:
6314 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
6315 break;
6316#endif
6317#ifdef INET6
6318 case AF_INET6:
6319 net->mtu += SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
6320 break;
6321#endif
6322#if defined(__Userspace__)
6323 case AF_CONN:
6324 net->mtu += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
6325 break;
6326#endif
6327 default:
6328 break;
6329 }
6330 if (net->mtu < stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu) {
6331 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
6332 }
6333 }
6334 }
6335 if (paddrp->spp_pathmtu > 0) {
6336 stcb->asoc.default_mtu = paddrp->spp_pathmtu;
6337 }
6338 sctp_stcb_feature_on(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_NOT_PMTUD);
6339 }
6340 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_PMTUD_ENABLE) {
6341 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6342 if (!SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->pmtu_timer.timer)) {
6343 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, inp, stcb, net);
6344 }
6345 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD;
6346 }
6347 stcb->asoc.default_mtu = 0;
6348 sctp_stcb_feature_off(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_NOT_PMTUD);
6349 }
6350 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_DSCP) {
6351 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6352 net->dscp = paddrp->spp_dscp & 0xfc;
6353 net->dscp |= 0x01;
6354 }
6355 stcb->asoc.default_dscp = paddrp->spp_dscp & 0xfc;
6356 stcb->asoc.default_dscp |= 0x01;
6357 }
6358#ifdef INET6
6359 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_IPV6_FLOWLABEL) {
6360 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
6361 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6362 net->flowlabel = paddrp->spp_ipv6_flowlabel & 0x000fffff;
6363 net->flowlabel |= 0x80000000;
6364 }
6365 }
6366 stcb->asoc.default_flowlabel = paddrp->spp_ipv6_flowlabel & 0x000fffff;
6367 stcb->asoc.default_flowlabel |= 0x80000000;
6368 }
6369#endif
6370 }
6371 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6372 } else {
6373 /************************NO TCB, SET TO default stuff ******************/
6374 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
6375 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
6376 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
6377 (paddrp->spp_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
6378 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
6379 /*
6380 * For the TOS/FLOWLABEL stuff you set it
6381 * with the options on the socket
6382 */
6383 if (paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt > 0) {
6384 inp->sctp_ep.def_net_failure = paddrp->spp_pathmaxrxt;
6385 }
6386
6387 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_TIME_IS_ZERO)
6388 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_HEARTBEAT] = 0;
6389 else if (paddrp->spp_hbinterval != 0) {
6390 if (paddrp->spp_hbinterval > SCTP_MAX_HB_INTERVAL)
6391 paddrp->spp_hbinterval= SCTP_MAX_HB_INTERVAL;
6392 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_HEARTBEAT] = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(paddrp->spp_hbinterval);
6393 }
6394
6395 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_ENABLE) {
6396 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_TIME_IS_ZERO) {
6397 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_HEARTBEAT] = 0;
6398 } else if (paddrp->spp_hbinterval) {
6399 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_timeoutticks[SCTP_TIMER_HEARTBEAT] = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(paddrp->spp_hbinterval);
6400 }
6401 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONOT_HEARTBEAT);
6402 } else if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_HB_DISABLE) {
6403 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONOT_HEARTBEAT);
6404 }
6405 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_PMTUD_ENABLE) {
6406 inp->sctp_ep.default_mtu = 0;
6407 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_NOT_PMTUD);
6408 } else if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_PMTUD_DISABLE) {
6409 if (paddrp->spp_pathmtu > 0) {
6410 inp->sctp_ep.default_mtu = paddrp->spp_pathmtu;
6411 }
6412 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_NOT_PMTUD);
6413 }
6414 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_DSCP) {
6415 inp->sctp_ep.default_dscp = paddrp->spp_dscp & 0xfc;
6416 inp->sctp_ep.default_dscp |= 0x01;
6417 }
6418#ifdef INET6
6419 if (paddrp->spp_flags & SPP_IPV6_FLOWLABEL) {
6420 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
6421 inp->sctp_ep.default_flowlabel = paddrp->spp_ipv6_flowlabel & 0x000fffff;
6422 inp->sctp_ep.default_flowlabel |= 0x80000000;
6423 }
6424 }
6425#endif
6426 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
6427 } else {
6428 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6429 error = EINVAL;
6430 }
6431 }
6432 break;
6433 }
6434 case SCTP_RTOINFO:
6435 {
6436 struct sctp_rtoinfo *srto;
6437 uint32_t new_init, new_min, new_max;
6438
6439 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(srto, optval, struct sctp_rtoinfo, optsize);
6440 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, srto->srto_assoc_id);
6441
6442 if (stcb) {
6443 if (srto->srto_initial)
6444 new_init = srto->srto_initial;
6445 else
6446 new_init = stcb->asoc.initial_rto;
6447 if (srto->srto_max)
6448 new_max = srto->srto_max;
6449 else
6450 new_max = stcb->asoc.maxrto;
6451 if (srto->srto_min)
6452 new_min = srto->srto_min;
6453 else
6454 new_min = stcb->asoc.minrto;
6455 if ((new_min <= new_init) && (new_init <= new_max)) {
6456 stcb->asoc.initial_rto = new_init;
6457 stcb->asoc.maxrto = new_max;
6458 stcb->asoc.minrto = new_min;
6459 } else {
6460 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6461 error = EINVAL;
6462 }
6463 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6464 } else {
6465 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
6466 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
6467 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
6468 (srto->srto_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
6469 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
6470 if (srto->srto_initial)
6471 new_init = srto->srto_initial;
6472 else
6473 new_init = inp->sctp_ep.initial_rto;
6474 if (srto->srto_max)
6475 new_max = srto->srto_max;
6476 else
6477 new_max = inp->sctp_ep.sctp_maxrto;
6478 if (srto->srto_min)
6479 new_min = srto->srto_min;
6480 else
6481 new_min = inp->sctp_ep.sctp_minrto;
6482 if ((new_min <= new_init) && (new_init <= new_max)) {
6483 inp->sctp_ep.initial_rto = new_init;
6484 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_maxrto = new_max;
6485 inp->sctp_ep.sctp_minrto = new_min;
6486 } else {
6487 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6488 error = EINVAL;
6489 }
6490 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
6491 } else {
6492 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6493 error = EINVAL;
6494 }
6495 }
6496 break;
6497 }
6498 case SCTP_ASSOCINFO:
6499 {
6500 struct sctp_assocparams *sasoc;
6501
6502 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(sasoc, optval, struct sctp_assocparams, optsize);
6503 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, sasoc->sasoc_assoc_id);
6504 if (sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life > 0) {
6505 /* boundary check the cookie life */
6506 if (sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life < SCTP_MIN_COOKIE_LIFE) {
6507 sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life = SCTP_MIN_COOKIE_LIFE;
6508 }
6509 if (sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life > SCTP_MAX_COOKIE_LIFE) {
6510 sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life = SCTP_MAX_COOKIE_LIFE;
6511 }
6512 }
6513 if (stcb) {
6514 if (sasoc->sasoc_asocmaxrxt > 0) {
6515 stcb->asoc.max_send_times = sasoc->sasoc_asocmaxrxt;
6516 }
6517 if (sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life > 0) {
6518 stcb->asoc.cookie_life = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life);
6519 }
6520 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6521 } else {
6522 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
6523 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
6524 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
6525 (sasoc->sasoc_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
6526 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
6527 if (sasoc->sasoc_asocmaxrxt > 0) {
6528 inp->sctp_ep.max_send_times = sasoc->sasoc_asocmaxrxt;
6529 }
6530 if (sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life > 0) {
6531 inp->sctp_ep.def_cookie_life = sctp_msecs_to_ticks(sasoc->sasoc_cookie_life);
6532 }
6533 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
6534 } else {
6535 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6536 error = EINVAL;
6537 }
6538 }
6539 break;
6540 }
6541 case SCTP_INITMSG:
6542 {
6543 struct sctp_initmsg *sinit;
6544
6545 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(sinit, optval, struct sctp_initmsg, optsize);
6546 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
6547 if (sinit->sinit_num_ostreams)
6548 inp->sctp_ep.pre_open_stream_count = sinit->sinit_num_ostreams;
6549
6550 if (sinit->sinit_max_instreams)
6551 inp->sctp_ep.max_open_streams_intome = sinit->sinit_max_instreams;
6552
6553 if (sinit->sinit_max_attempts)
6554 inp->sctp_ep.max_init_times = sinit->sinit_max_attempts;
6555
6556 if (sinit->sinit_max_init_timeo)
6557 inp->sctp_ep.initial_init_rto_max = sinit->sinit_max_init_timeo;
6558 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
6559 break;
6560 }
6561 case SCTP_PRIMARY_ADDR:
6562 {
6563 struct sctp_setprim *spa;
6564 struct sctp_nets *net;
6565 struct sockaddr *addr;
6566#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
6567 struct sockaddr_in sin_store;
6568#endif
6569
6570 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(spa, optval, struct sctp_setprim, optsize);
6571 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, spa->ssp_assoc_id);
6572
6573#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
6574 if (spa->ssp_addr.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
6575 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
6576
6577 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&spa->ssp_addr;
6578 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
6579 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin_store, sin6);
6580 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sin_store;
6581 } else {
6582 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&spa->ssp_addr;
6583 }
6584 } else {
6585 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&spa->ssp_addr;
6586 }
6587#else
6588 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&spa->ssp_addr;
6589#endif
6590 if (stcb != NULL) {
6591 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, addr);
6592 } else {
6593 /* We increment here since sctp_findassociation_ep_addr() wil
6594 * do a decrement if it finds the stcb as long as the locked
6595 * tcb (last argument) is NOT a TCB.. aka NULL.
6596 */
6597 net = NULL;
6598 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
6599 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, addr,
6600 &net, NULL, NULL);
6601 if (stcb == NULL) {
6602 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
6603 }
6604 }
6605
6606 if ((stcb != NULL) && (net != NULL)) {
6607 if (net != stcb->asoc.primary_destination) {
6608 if (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED)) {
6609 /* Ok we need to set it */
6610 if (sctp_set_primary_addr(stcb, (struct sockaddr *)NULL, net) == 0) {
6611 if ((stcb->asoc.alternate) &&
6612 (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF)) &&
6613 (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE)) {
6614 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
6615 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
6616 }
6617 } else {
6618 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6619 error = EINVAL;
6620 }
6621 } else {
6622 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6623 error = EINVAL;
6624 }
6625 }
6626 } else {
6627 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6628 error = EINVAL;
6629 }
6630 if (stcb != NULL) {
6631 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6632 }
6633 break;
6634 }
6635 case SCTP_SET_DYNAMIC_PRIMARY:
6636 {
6637 union sctp_sockstore *ss;
6638#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
6639 int i, fnd = 0;
6640#endif
6641#if !defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6642#if defined(__APPLE__)
6643 struct proc *proc;
6644#endif
6645#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
6646 error = priv_check(curthread,
6647 PRIV_NETINET_RESERVEDPORT);
6648#elif defined(__APPLE__)
6649 proc = (struct proc *)p;
6650 if (p) {
6651 error = suser(proc->p_ucred, &proc->p_acflag);
6652 } else {
6653 break;
6654 }
6655#else
6656 error = suser(p, 0);
6657#endif
6658 if (error)
6659 break;
6660#endif
6661
6662 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(ss, optval, union sctp_sockstore, optsize);
6663 /* SUPER USER CHECK? */
6664#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
6665 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
6666 if (vrf_id == inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) {
6667 fnd = 1;
6668 break;
6669 }
6670 }
6671 if (!fnd) {
6672 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6673 error = EINVAL;
6674 break;
6675 }
6676#endif
6677 error = sctp_dynamic_set_primary(&ss->sa, vrf_id);
6678 break;
6679 }
6680 case SCTP_SET_PEER_PRIMARY_ADDR:
6681 {
6682 struct sctp_setpeerprim *sspp;
6683 struct sockaddr *addr;
6684#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
6685 struct sockaddr_in sin_store;
6686#endif
6687
6688 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(sspp, optval, struct sctp_setpeerprim, optsize);
6689 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, sspp->sspp_assoc_id);
6690 if (stcb != NULL) {
6691 struct sctp_ifa *ifa;
6692
6693#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
6694 if (sspp->sspp_addr.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
6695 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
6696
6697 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&sspp->sspp_addr;
6698 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
6699 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin_store, sin6);
6700 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sin_store;
6701 } else {
6702 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sspp->sspp_addr;
6703 }
6704 } else {
6705 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sspp->sspp_addr;
6706 }
6707#else
6708 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sspp->sspp_addr;
6709#endif
6710 ifa = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(addr, stcb->asoc.vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_NOT_LOCKED);
6711 if (ifa == NULL) {
6712 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6713 error = EINVAL;
6714 goto out_of_it;
6715 }
6716 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) == 0) {
6717 /* Must validate the ifa found is in our ep */
6718 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
6719 int found = 0;
6720
6721 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
6722 if (laddr->ifa == NULL) {
6723 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "%s: NULL ifa\n",
6724 __func__);
6725 continue;
6726 }
6727 if ((sctp_is_addr_restricted(stcb, laddr->ifa)) &&
6728 (!sctp_is_addr_pending(stcb, laddr->ifa))) {
6729 continue;
6730 }
6731 if (laddr->ifa == ifa) {
6732 found = 1;
6733 break;
6734 }
6735 }
6736 if (!found) {
6737 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6738 error = EINVAL;
6739 goto out_of_it;
6740 }
6741#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6742 } else {
6743 switch (addr->sa_family) {
6744#ifdef INET
6745 case AF_INET:
6746 {
6747 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
6748
6749 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
6750 if (prison_check_ip4(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
6751 &sin->sin_addr) != 0) {
6752 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6753 error = EINVAL;
6754 goto out_of_it;
6755 }
6756 break;
6757 }
6758#endif
6759#ifdef INET6
6760 case AF_INET6:
6761 {
6762 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
6763
6764 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
6765 if (prison_check_ip6(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
6766 &sin6->sin6_addr) != 0) {
6767 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6768 error = EINVAL;
6769 goto out_of_it;
6770 }
6771 break;
6772 }
6773#endif
6774 default:
6775 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6776 error = EINVAL;
6777 goto out_of_it;
6778 }
6779#endif
6780 }
6781 if (sctp_set_primary_ip_address_sa(stcb, addr) != 0) {
6782 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6783 error = EINVAL;
6784 }
6785 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_SOCKOPT, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6786 out_of_it:
6787 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6788 } else {
6789 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6790 error = EINVAL;
6791 }
6792 break;
6793 }
6794 case SCTP_BINDX_ADD_ADDR:
6795 {
6796 struct sockaddr *sa;
6797#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6798 struct thread *td;
6799
6800 td = (struct thread *)p;
6801#endif
6802 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(sa, optval, struct sockaddr, optsize);
6803#ifdef INET
6804 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET) {
6805 if (optsize < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
6806 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6807 error = EINVAL;
6808 break;
6809 }
6810#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6811 if (td != NULL &&
6812 (error = prison_local_ip4(td->td_ucred, &(((struct sockaddr_in *)sa)->sin_addr)))) {
6813 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
6814 break;
6815 }
6816#endif
6817 } else
6818#endif
6819#ifdef INET6
6820 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6821 if (optsize < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
6822 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6823 error = EINVAL;
6824 break;
6825 }
6826#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6827 if (td != NULL &&
6828 (error = prison_local_ip6(td->td_ucred,
6829 &(((struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa)->sin6_addr),
6830 (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp) != 0))) != 0) {
6831 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
6832 break;
6833 }
6834#endif
6835 } else
6836#endif
6837 {
6838 error = EAFNOSUPPORT;
6839 break;
6840 }
6841 sctp_bindx_add_address(so, inp, sa, vrf_id, &error, p);
6842 break;
6843 }
6844 case SCTP_BINDX_REM_ADDR:
6845 {
6846 struct sockaddr *sa;
6847#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6848 struct thread *td;
6849 td = (struct thread *)p;
6850
6851#endif
6852 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(sa, optval, struct sockaddr, optsize);
6853#ifdef INET
6854 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET) {
6855 if (optsize < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
6856 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6857 error = EINVAL;
6858 break;
6859 }
6860#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6861 if (td != NULL &&
6862 (error = prison_local_ip4(td->td_ucred, &(((struct sockaddr_in *)sa)->sin_addr)))) {
6863 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
6864 break;
6865 }
6866#endif
6867 } else
6868#endif
6869#ifdef INET6
6870 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
6871 if (optsize < sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
6872 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6873 error = EINVAL;
6874 break;
6875 }
6876#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6877 if (td != NULL &&
6878 (error = prison_local_ip6(td->td_ucred,
6879 &(((struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa)->sin6_addr),
6880 (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp) != 0))) != 0) {
6881 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
6882 break;
6883 }
6884#endif
6885 } else
6886#endif
6887 {
6888 error = EAFNOSUPPORT;
6889 break;
6890 }
6891 sctp_bindx_delete_address(inp, sa, vrf_id, &error);
6892 break;
6893 }
6894#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6895 case SCTP_LISTEN_FIX:
6896 /* only applies to one-to-many sockets */
6897 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) {
6898 /* make sure the ACCEPTCONN flag is OFF */
6899 so->so_options &= ~SO_ACCEPTCONN;
6900 } else {
6901 /* otherwise, not allowed */
6902 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6903 error = EINVAL;
6904 }
6905 break;
6906#endif
6907 case SCTP_EVENT:
6908 {
6909 struct sctp_event *event;
6910 uint32_t event_type;
6911
6912 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(event, optval, struct sctp_event, optsize);
6913 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, event->se_assoc_id);
6914 switch (event->se_type) {
6915 case SCTP_ASSOC_CHANGE:
6916 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVASSOCEVNT;
6917 break;
6918 case SCTP_PEER_ADDR_CHANGE:
6919 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVPADDREVNT;
6920 break;
6921 case SCTP_REMOTE_ERROR:
6922 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVPEERERR;
6923 break;
6924 case SCTP_SEND_FAILED:
6925 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVSENDFAILEVNT;
6926 break;
6927 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_EVENT:
6928 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVSHUTDOWNEVNT;
6929 break;
6930 case SCTP_ADAPTATION_INDICATION:
6931 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ADAPTATIONEVNT;
6932 break;
6933 case SCTP_PARTIAL_DELIVERY_EVENT:
6934 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PDAPIEVNT;
6935 break;
6936 case SCTP_AUTHENTICATION_EVENT:
6937 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTHEVNT;
6938 break;
6939 case SCTP_STREAM_RESET_EVENT:
6940 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_STREAM_RESETEVNT;
6941 break;
6942 case SCTP_SENDER_DRY_EVENT:
6943 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DRYEVNT;
6944 break;
6945 case SCTP_NOTIFICATIONS_STOPPED_EVENT:
6946 event_type = 0;
6947 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOTSUP);
6948 error = ENOTSUP;
6949 break;
6950 case SCTP_ASSOC_RESET_EVENT:
6951 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ASSOC_RESETEVNT;
6952 break;
6953 case SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_EVENT:
6954 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_STREAM_CHANGEEVNT;
6955 break;
6956 case SCTP_SEND_FAILED_EVENT:
6957 event_type = SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT;
6958 break;
6959 default:
6960 event_type = 0;
6961 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
6962 error = EINVAL;
6963 break;
6964 }
6965 if (event_type > 0) {
6966 if (stcb) {
6967 if (event->se_on) {
6968 sctp_stcb_feature_on(inp, stcb, event_type);
6969 if (event_type == SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DRYEVNT) {
6970 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.send_queue) &&
6971 TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue) &&
6972 (stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt == 0)) {
6973 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENDER_DRY, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6974 }
6975 }
6976 } else {
6977 sctp_stcb_feature_off(inp, stcb, event_type);
6978 }
6979 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6980 } else {
6981 /*
6982 * We don't want to send up a storm of events,
6983 * so return an error for sender dry events
6984 */
6985 if ((event_type == SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DRYEVNT) &&
6986 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
6987 ((event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC) ||
6988 (event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_CURRENT_ASSOC))) {
6989 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOTSUP);
6990 error = ENOTSUP;
6991 break;
6992 }
6993 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
6994 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
6995 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
6996 ((event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC) ||
6997 (event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC)))) {
6998 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
6999 if (event->se_on) {
7000 sctp_feature_on(inp, event_type);
7001 } else {
7002 sctp_feature_off(inp, event_type);
7003 }
7004 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7005 }
7006 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7007 ((event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_CURRENT_ASSOC) ||
7008 (event->se_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC))) {
7009 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
7010 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
7011 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
7012 if (event->se_on) {
7013 sctp_stcb_feature_on(inp, stcb, event_type);
7014 } else {
7015 sctp_stcb_feature_off(inp, stcb, event_type);
7016 }
7017 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7018 }
7019 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
7020 }
7021 }
7022 } else {
7023 if (stcb) {
7024 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7025 }
7026 }
7027 break;
7028 }
7029 case SCTP_RECVRCVINFO:
7030 {
7031 int *onoff;
7032
7033 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(onoff, optval, int, optsize);
7034 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7035 if (*onoff != 0) {
7036 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVRCVINFO);
7037 } else {
7038 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVRCVINFO);
7039 }
7040 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7041 break;
7042 }
7043 case SCTP_RECVNXTINFO:
7044 {
7045 int *onoff;
7046
7047 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(onoff, optval, int, optsize);
7048 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7049 if (*onoff != 0) {
7050 sctp_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNXTINFO);
7051 } else {
7052 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNXTINFO);
7053 }
7054 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7055 break;
7056 }
7057 case SCTP_DEFAULT_SNDINFO:
7058 {
7059 struct sctp_sndinfo *info;
7060 uint16_t policy;
7061
7062 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(info, optval, struct sctp_sndinfo, optsize);
7063 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, info->snd_assoc_id);
7064
7065 if (stcb) {
7066 if (info->snd_sid < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
7067 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_stream = info->snd_sid;
7068 policy = PR_SCTP_POLICY(stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags);
7069 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags = info->snd_flags;
7070 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags |= policy;
7071 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_ppid = info->snd_ppid;
7072 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_context = info->snd_context;
7073 } else {
7074 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7075 error = EINVAL;
7076 }
7077 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7078 } else {
7079 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7080 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7081 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7082 ((info->snd_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC) ||
7083 (info->snd_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC)))) {
7084 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7085 inp->def_send.sinfo_stream = info->snd_sid;
7086 policy = PR_SCTP_POLICY(inp->def_send.sinfo_flags);
7087 inp->def_send.sinfo_flags = info->snd_flags;
7088 inp->def_send.sinfo_flags |= policy;
7089 inp->def_send.sinfo_ppid = info->snd_ppid;
7090 inp->def_send.sinfo_context = info->snd_context;
7091 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7092 }
7093 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7094 ((info->snd_assoc_id == SCTP_CURRENT_ASSOC) ||
7095 (info->snd_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC))) {
7096 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
7097 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
7098 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
7099 if (info->snd_sid < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
7100 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_stream = info->snd_sid;
7101 policy = PR_SCTP_POLICY(stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags);
7102 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags = info->snd_flags;
7103 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags |= policy;
7104 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_ppid = info->snd_ppid;
7105 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_context = info->snd_context;
7106 }
7107 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7108 }
7109 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
7110 }
7111 }
7112 break;
7113 }
7114 case SCTP_DEFAULT_PRINFO:
7115 {
7116 struct sctp_default_prinfo *info;
7117
7118 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(info, optval, struct sctp_default_prinfo, optsize);
7119 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, info->pr_assoc_id);
7120
7121 if (info->pr_policy > SCTP_PR_SCTP_MAX) {
7122 if (stcb) {
7123 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7124 }
7125 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7126 error = EINVAL;
7127 break;
7128 }
7129 if (stcb) {
7130 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags &= 0xfff0;
7131 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags |= info->pr_policy;
7132 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_timetolive = info->pr_value;
7133 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7134 } else {
7135 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7136 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7137 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7138 ((info->pr_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC) ||
7139 (info->pr_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC)))) {
7140 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7141 inp->def_send.sinfo_flags &= 0xfff0;
7142 inp->def_send.sinfo_flags |= info->pr_policy;
7143 inp->def_send.sinfo_timetolive = info->pr_value;
7144 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7145 }
7146 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7147 ((info->pr_assoc_id == SCTP_CURRENT_ASSOC) ||
7148 (info->pr_assoc_id == SCTP_ALL_ASSOC))) {
7149 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
7150 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, &inp->sctp_asoc_list, sctp_tcblist) {
7151 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
7152 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags &= 0xfff0;
7153 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_flags |= info->pr_policy;
7154 stcb->asoc.def_send.sinfo_timetolive = info->pr_value;
7155 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7156 }
7157 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
7158 }
7159 }
7160 break;
7161 }
7162 case SCTP_PEER_ADDR_THLDS:
7163 /* Applies to the specific association */
7164 {
7165 struct sctp_paddrthlds *thlds;
7166 struct sctp_nets *net;
7167 struct sockaddr *addr;
7168#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7169 struct sockaddr_in sin_store;
7170#endif
7171
7172 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(thlds, optval, struct sctp_paddrthlds, optsize);
7173 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, thlds->spt_assoc_id);
7174
7175#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7176 if (thlds->spt_address.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
7177 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7178
7179 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&thlds->spt_address;
7180 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7181 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin_store, sin6);
7182 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sin_store;
7183 } else {
7184 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&thlds->spt_address;
7185 }
7186 } else {
7187 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&thlds->spt_address;
7188 }
7189#else
7190 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&thlds->spt_address;
7191#endif
7192 if (stcb != NULL) {
7193 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, addr);
7194 } else {
7195 /* We increment here since sctp_findassociation_ep_addr() wil
7196 * do a decrement if it finds the stcb as long as the locked
7197 * tcb (last argument) is NOT a TCB.. aka NULL.
7198 */
7199 net = NULL;
7200 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
7201 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, addr,
7202 &net, NULL, NULL);
7203 if (stcb == NULL) {
7204 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
7205 }
7206 }
7207 if ((stcb != NULL) && (net == NULL)) {
7208#ifdef INET
7209 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET) {
7210 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
7211
7212 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
7213 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr != INADDR_ANY) {
7214 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7215 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7216 error = EINVAL;
7217 break;
7218 }
7219 } else
7220#endif
7221#ifdef INET6
7222 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
7223 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7224
7225 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
7226 if (!IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7227 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7228 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7229 error = EINVAL;
7230 break;
7231 }
7232 } else
7233#endif
7234#if defined(__Userspace__)
7235 if (addr->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
7236 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
7237
7238 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)addr;
7239 if (sconn->sconn_addr != NULL) {
7240 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7241 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7242 error = EINVAL;
7243 break;
7244 }
7245 } else
7246#endif
7247 {
7248 error = EAFNOSUPPORT;
7249 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7250 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
7251 break;
7252 }
7253 }
7254 if (thlds->spt_pathcpthld != 0xffff) {
7255 if (stcb != NULL) {
7256 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7257 }
7258 error = EINVAL;
7259 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
7260 break;
7261 }
7262 if (stcb != NULL) {
7263 if (net != NULL) {
7264 net->failure_threshold = thlds->spt_pathmaxrxt;
7265 net->pf_threshold = thlds->spt_pathpfthld;
7266 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) {
7267 if ((net->error_count > net->failure_threshold) ||
7268 (net->error_count <= net->pf_threshold)) {
7269 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_PF;
7270 }
7271 } else {
7272 if ((net->error_count > net->pf_threshold) &&
7273 (net->error_count <= net->failure_threshold)) {
7274 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_PF;
7275 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7276 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT,
7277 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
7278 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_17);
7279 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
7280 }
7281 }
7282 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE) {
7283 if (net->error_count > net->failure_threshold) {
7284 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
7285 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7286 }
7287 } else {
7288 if (net->error_count <= net->failure_threshold) {
7289 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
7290 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7291 }
7292 }
7293 } else {
7294 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
7295 net->failure_threshold = thlds->spt_pathmaxrxt;
7296 net->pf_threshold = thlds->spt_pathpfthld;
7297 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) {
7298 if ((net->error_count > net->failure_threshold) ||
7299 (net->error_count <= net->pf_threshold)) {
7300 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_PF;
7301 }
7302 } else {
7303 if ((net->error_count > net->pf_threshold) &&
7304 (net->error_count <= net->failure_threshold)) {
7305 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_PF;
7306 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7307 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT,
7308 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
7309 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_18);
7310 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
7311 }
7312 }
7313 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE) {
7314 if (net->error_count > net->failure_threshold) {
7315 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
7316 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7317 }
7318 } else {
7319 if (net->error_count <= net->failure_threshold) {
7320 net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
7321 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP, stcb, 0, net, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
7322 }
7323 }
7324 }
7325 stcb->asoc.def_net_failure = thlds->spt_pathmaxrxt;
7326 stcb->asoc.def_net_pf_threshold = thlds->spt_pathpfthld;
7327 }
7328 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7329 } else {
7330 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7331 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7332 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7333 (thlds->spt_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7334 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7335 inp->sctp_ep.def_net_failure = thlds->spt_pathmaxrxt;
7336 inp->sctp_ep.def_net_pf_threshold = thlds->spt_pathpfthld;
7337 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7338 } else {
7339 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7340 error = EINVAL;
7341 }
7342 }
7343 break;
7344 }
7345 case SCTP_REMOTE_UDP_ENCAPS_PORT:
7346 {
7347 struct sctp_udpencaps *encaps;
7348 struct sctp_nets *net;
7349 struct sockaddr *addr;
7350#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7351 struct sockaddr_in sin_store;
7352#endif
7353
7354 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(encaps, optval, struct sctp_udpencaps, optsize);
7355 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, encaps->sue_assoc_id);
7356
7357#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7358 if (encaps->sue_address.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
7359 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7360
7361 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&encaps->sue_address;
7362 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7363 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin_store, sin6);
7364 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&sin_store;
7365 } else {
7366 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&encaps->sue_address;
7367 }
7368 } else {
7369 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&encaps->sue_address;
7370 }
7371#else
7372 addr = (struct sockaddr *)&encaps->sue_address;
7373#endif
7374 if (stcb != NULL) {
7375 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, addr);
7376 } else {
7377 /* We increment here since sctp_findassociation_ep_addr() wil
7378 * do a decrement if it finds the stcb as long as the locked
7379 * tcb (last argument) is NOT a TCB.. aka NULL.
7380 */
7381 net = NULL;
7382 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
7383 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, addr, &net, NULL, NULL);
7384 if (stcb == NULL) {
7385 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
7386 }
7387 }
7388 if ((stcb != NULL) && (net == NULL)) {
7389#ifdef INET
7390 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET) {
7391 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
7392
7393 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
7394 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr != INADDR_ANY) {
7395 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7396 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7397 error = EINVAL;
7398 break;
7399 }
7400 } else
7401#endif
7402#ifdef INET6
7403 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
7404 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7405
7406 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
7407 if (!IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7408 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7409 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7410 error = EINVAL;
7411 break;
7412 }
7413 } else
7414#endif
7415#if defined(__Userspace__)
7416 if (addr->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
7417 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
7418
7419 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)addr;
7420 if (sconn->sconn_addr != NULL) {
7421 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7422 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7423 error = EINVAL;
7424 break;
7425 }
7426 } else
7427#endif
7428 {
7429 error = EAFNOSUPPORT;
7430 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7431 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
7432 break;
7433 }
7434 }
7435
7436 if (stcb != NULL) {
7437 if (net != NULL) {
7438 net->port = encaps->sue_port;
7439 } else {
7440 stcb->asoc.port = encaps->sue_port;
7441 }
7442 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7443 } else {
7444 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7445 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7446 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7447 (encaps->sue_assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7448 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7449 inp->sctp_ep.port = encaps->sue_port;
7450 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7451 } else {
7452 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7453 error = EINVAL;
7454 }
7455 }
7456 break;
7457 }
7458 case SCTP_ECN_SUPPORTED:
7459 {
7460 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7461
7462 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7463 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7464
7465 if (stcb) {
7466 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7467 error = EINVAL;
7468 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7469 } else {
7470 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7471 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7472 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7473 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7474 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7475 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7476 inp->ecn_supported = 0;
7477 } else {
7478 inp->ecn_supported = 1;
7479 }
7480 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7481 } else {
7482 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7483 error = EINVAL;
7484 }
7485 }
7486 break;
7487 }
7488 case SCTP_PR_SUPPORTED:
7489 {
7490 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7491
7492 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7493 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7494
7495 if (stcb) {
7496 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7497 error = EINVAL;
7498 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7499 } else {
7500 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7501 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7502 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7503 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7504 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7505 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7506 inp->prsctp_supported = 0;
7507 } else {
7508 inp->prsctp_supported = 1;
7509 }
7510 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7511 } else {
7512 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7513 error = EINVAL;
7514 }
7515 }
7516 break;
7517 }
7518 case SCTP_AUTH_SUPPORTED:
7519 {
7520 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7521
7522 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7523 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7524
7525 if (stcb) {
7526 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7527 error = EINVAL;
7528 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7529 } else {
7530 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7531 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7532 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7533 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7534 if ((av->assoc_value == 0) &&
7535 (inp->asconf_supported == 1)) {
7536 /* AUTH is required for ASCONF */
7537 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7538 error = EINVAL;
7539 } else {
7540 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7541 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7542 inp->auth_supported = 0;
7543 } else {
7544 inp->auth_supported = 1;
7545 }
7546 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7547 }
7548 } else {
7549 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7550 error = EINVAL;
7551 }
7552 }
7553 break;
7554 }
7555 case SCTP_ASCONF_SUPPORTED:
7556 {
7557 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7558
7559 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7560 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7561
7562 if (stcb) {
7563 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7564 error = EINVAL;
7565 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7566 } else {
7567 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7568 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7569 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7570 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7571 if ((av->assoc_value != 0) &&
7572 (inp->auth_supported == 0)) {
7573 /* AUTH is required for ASCONF */
7574 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7575 error = EINVAL;
7576 } else {
7577 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7578 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7579 inp->asconf_supported = 0;
7580 sctp_auth_delete_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF,
7581 inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
7582 sctp_auth_delete_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF_ACK,
7583 inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
7584 } else {
7585 inp->asconf_supported = 1;
7586 sctp_auth_add_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF,
7587 inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
7588 sctp_auth_add_chunk(SCTP_ASCONF_ACK,
7589 inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
7590 }
7591 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7592 }
7593 } else {
7594 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7595 error = EINVAL;
7596 }
7597 }
7598 break;
7599 }
7600 case SCTP_RECONFIG_SUPPORTED:
7601 {
7602 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7603
7604 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7605 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7606
7607 if (stcb) {
7608 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7609 error = EINVAL;
7610 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7611 } else {
7612 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7613 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7614 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7615 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7616 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7617 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7618 inp->reconfig_supported = 0;
7619 } else {
7620 inp->reconfig_supported = 1;
7621 }
7622 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7623 } else {
7624 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7625 error = EINVAL;
7626 }
7627 }
7628 break;
7629 }
7630 case SCTP_NRSACK_SUPPORTED:
7631 {
7632 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7633
7634 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7635 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7636
7637 if (stcb) {
7638 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7639 error = EINVAL;
7640 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7641 } else {
7642 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7643 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7644 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7645 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7646 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7647 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7648 inp->nrsack_supported = 0;
7649 } else {
7650 inp->nrsack_supported = 1;
7651 }
7652 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7653 } else {
7654 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7655 error = EINVAL;
7656 }
7657 }
7658 break;
7659 }
7660 case SCTP_PKTDROP_SUPPORTED:
7661 {
7662 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7663
7664 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7665 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7666
7667 if (stcb) {
7668 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7669 error = EINVAL;
7670 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7671 } else {
7672 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7673 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7674 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7675 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7676 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7677 if (av->assoc_value == 0) {
7678 inp->pktdrop_supported = 0;
7679 } else {
7680 inp->pktdrop_supported = 1;
7681 }
7682 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7683 } else {
7684 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7685 error = EINVAL;
7686 }
7687 }
7688 break;
7689 }
7690 case SCTP_MAX_CWND:
7691 {
7692 struct sctp_assoc_value *av;
7693 struct sctp_nets *net;
7694
7695 SCTP_CHECK_AND_CAST(av, optval, struct sctp_assoc_value, optsize);
7696 SCTP_FIND_STCB(inp, stcb, av->assoc_id);
7697
7698 if (stcb) {
7699 stcb->asoc.max_cwnd = av->assoc_value;
7700 if (stcb->asoc.max_cwnd > 0) {
7701 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
7702 if ((net->cwnd > stcb->asoc.max_cwnd) &&
7703 (net->cwnd > (net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr)))) {
7704 net->cwnd = stcb->asoc.max_cwnd;
7705 if (net->cwnd < (net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr))) {
7706 net->cwnd = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
7707 }
7708 }
7709 }
7710 }
7711 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7712 } else {
7713 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7714 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
7715 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
7716 (av->assoc_id == SCTP_FUTURE_ASSOC))) {
7717 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7718 inp->max_cwnd = av->assoc_value;
7719 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7720 } else {
7721 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7722 error = EINVAL;
7723 }
7724 }
7725 break;
7726 }
7727 default:
7728 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOPROTOOPT);
7729 error = ENOPROTOOPT;
7730 break;
7731 } /* end switch (opt) */
7732 return (error);
7733}
7734
7735#if !defined(__Userspace__)
7736int
7737sctp_ctloutput(struct socket *so, struct sockopt *sopt)
7738{
7739#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
7740 struct epoch_tracker et;
7741 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7742#endif
7743 void *optval = NULL;
7744 void *p;
7745 size_t optsize = 0;
7746 int error = 0;
7747
7748#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
7749 if ((sopt->sopt_level == SOL_SOCKET) &&
7750 (sopt->sopt_name == SO_SETFIB)) {
7751 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
7752 if (inp == NULL) {
7753 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(so->so_pcb, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOBUFS);
7754 return (EINVAL);
7755 }
7756 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
7757 inp->fibnum = so->so_fibnum;
7758 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
7759 return (0);
7760 }
7761#endif
7762 if (sopt->sopt_level != IPPROTO_SCTP) {
7763 /* wrong proto level... send back up to IP */
7764#ifdef INET6
7765 if (INP_CHECK_SOCKAF(so, AF_INET6))
7766 error = ip6_ctloutput(so, sopt);
7767#endif /* INET6 */
7768#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7769 else
7770#endif
7771#ifdef INET
7772 error = ip_ctloutput(so, sopt);
7773#endif
7774 return (error);
7775 }
7776 optsize = sopt->sopt_valsize;
7777 if (optsize > SCTP_SOCKET_OPTION_LIMIT) {
7778 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(so->so_pcb, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOBUFS);
7779 return (ENOBUFS);
7780 }
7781 if (optsize) {
7782 SCTP_MALLOC(optval, void *, optsize, SCTP_M_SOCKOPT);
7783 if (optval == NULL) {
7784 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(so->so_pcb, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOBUFS);
7785 return (ENOBUFS);
7786 }
7787 error = sooptcopyin(sopt, optval, optsize, optsize);
7788 if (error) {
7789 SCTP_FREE(optval, SCTP_M_SOCKOPT);
7790 goto out;
7791 }
7792 }
7793#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32)
7794 p = (void *)sopt->sopt_td;
7795#else
7796 p = (void *)sopt->sopt_p;
7797#endif
7798 if (sopt->sopt_dir == SOPT_SET) {
7799#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
7800 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
7801#endif
7802 error = sctp_setopt(so, sopt->sopt_name, optval, optsize, p);
7803#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
7804 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
7805#endif
7806 } else if (sopt->sopt_dir == SOPT_GET) {
7807 error = sctp_getopt(so, sopt->sopt_name, optval, &optsize, p);
7808 } else {
7809 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(so->so_pcb, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7810 error = EINVAL;
7811 }
7812 if ((error == 0) && (optval != NULL)) {
7813 error = sooptcopyout(sopt, optval, optsize);
7814 SCTP_FREE(optval, SCTP_M_SOCKOPT);
7815 } else if (optval != NULL) {
7816 SCTP_FREE(optval, SCTP_M_SOCKOPT);
7817 }
7818out:
7819 return (error);
7820}
7821#endif
7822
7823#ifdef INET
7824#if defined(__Userspace__)
7825int
7826sctp_connect(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr)
7827{
7828 void *p = NULL;
7829#elif defined(__FreeBSD__)
7830static int
7831sctp_connect(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr, struct thread *p)
7832{
7833#elif defined(__APPLE__)
7834static int
7835sctp_connect(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr, struct proc *p)
7836{
7837#elif defined(_WIN32)
7838static int
7839sctp_connect(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr, PKTHREAD p)
7840{
7841#else
7842static int
7843sctp_connect(struct socket *so, struct mbuf *nam, struct proc *p)
7844{
7845 struct sockaddr *addr = mtod(nam, struct sockaddr *);
7846
7847#endif
7848#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7849 struct epoch_tracker et;
7850#endif
7851#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
7852 int i, fnd = 0;
7853#endif
7854 int error = 0;
7855 int create_lock_on = 0;
7856 uint32_t vrf_id;
7857 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7858 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
7859
7860 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
7861 if (inp == NULL) {
7862 /* I made the same as TCP since we are not setup? */
7863 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7864 return (ECONNRESET);
7865 }
7866 if (addr == NULL) {
7867 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7868 return EINVAL;
7869 }
7870
7871#if defined(__Userspace__)
7872 /* TODO __Userspace__ falls into this code for IPv6 stuff at the moment... */
7873#endif
7874#if !defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__linux__) && !defined(__EMSCRIPTEN__)
7875 switch (addr->sa_family) {
7876#ifdef INET6
7877 case AF_INET6:
7878 {
7879#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7880 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7881
7882#endif
7883 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
7884 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7885 return (EINVAL);
7886 }
7887#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7888 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
7889 if (p != NULL && (error = prison_remote_ip6(p->td_ucred, &sin6->sin6_addr)) != 0) {
7890 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
7891 return (error);
7892 }
7893#endif
7894 break;
7895 }
7896#endif
7897#ifdef INET
7898 case AF_INET:
7899 {
7900#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7901 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
7902
7903#endif
7904#if !defined(_WIN32)
7905 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
7906 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7907 return (EINVAL);
7908 }
7909#endif
7910#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7911 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
7912 if (p != NULL && (error = prison_remote_ip4(p->td_ucred, &sin->sin_addr)) != 0) {
7913 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, error);
7914 return (error);
7915 }
7916#endif
7917 break;
7918 }
7919#endif
7920 default:
7921 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EAFNOSUPPORT);
7922 return (EAFNOSUPPORT);
7923 }
7924#endif
7925 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
7926 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK(inp);
7927 create_lock_on = 1;
7928#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7929 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
7930#endif
7931
7932 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
7933 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE)) {
7934 /* Should I really unlock ? */
7935 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EFAULT);
7936 error = EFAULT;
7937 goto out_now;
7938 }
7939#ifdef INET6
7940 if (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) &&
7941 (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6)) {
7942 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7943 error = EINVAL;
7944 goto out_now;
7945 }
7946#endif
7947#if defined(__Userspace__)
7948 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) &&
7949 (addr->sa_family != AF_CONN)) {
7950 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7951 error = EINVAL;
7952 goto out_now;
7953 }
7954#endif
7955 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) ==
7956 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
7957 /* Bind a ephemeral port */
7958 error = sctp_inpcb_bind(so, NULL, NULL, p);
7959 if (error) {
7960 goto out_now;
7961 }
7962 }
7963 /* Now do we connect? */
7964 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) &&
7965 (sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE))) {
7966 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
7967 error = EINVAL;
7968 goto out_now;
7969 }
7970 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
7971 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED)) {
7972 /* We are already connected AND the TCP model */
7973 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EADDRINUSE);
7974 error = EADDRINUSE;
7975 goto out_now;
7976 }
7977 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) {
7978 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
7979 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
7980 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
7981 } else {
7982 /* We increment here since sctp_findassociation_ep_addr() will
7983 * do a decrement if it finds the stcb as long as the locked
7984 * tcb (last argument) is NOT a TCB.. aka NULL.
7985 */
7986 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
7987 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, addr, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7988 if (stcb == NULL) {
7989 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
7990 } else {
7991 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7992 }
7993 }
7994 if (stcb != NULL) {
7995 /* Already have or am bring up an association */
7996 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EALREADY);
7997 error = EALREADY;
7998 goto out_now;
7999 }
8000
8001 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
8002#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
8003 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
8004 if (vrf_id == inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) {
8005 fnd = 1;
8006 break;
8007 }
8008 }
8009 if (!fnd) {
8010 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8011 error = EINVAL;
8012 goto out_now;
8013 }
8014#endif
8015 /* We are GOOD to go */
8016 stcb = sctp_aloc_assoc(inp, addr, &error, 0, vrf_id,
8017 inp->sctp_ep.pre_open_stream_count,
8018 inp->sctp_ep.port, p,
8019 SCTP_INITIALIZE_AUTH_PARAMS);
8020 if (stcb == NULL) {
8021 /* Gak! no memory */
8022 goto out_now;
8023 }
8024 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) {
8025 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
8026 /* Set the connected flag so we can queue data */
8027 soisconnecting(so);
8028 }
8029 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
8030 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&stcb->asoc.time_entered);
8031
8032 sctp_send_initiate(inp, stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
8033 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8034 out_now:
8035#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8036 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
8037#endif
8038 if (create_lock_on) {
8039 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
8040 }
8041 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
8042 return (error);
8043}
8044#endif
8045
8046#if defined(__Userspace__)
8047int
8048sctpconn_connect(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr *addr)
8049{
8050#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
8051 int i, fnd = 0;
8052#endif
8053 void *p = NULL;
8054 int error = 0;
8055 int create_lock_on = 0;
8056 uint32_t vrf_id;
8057 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8058 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
8059
8060 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
8061 if (inp == NULL) {
8062 /* I made the same as TCP since we are not setup? */
8063 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8064 return (ECONNRESET);
8065 }
8066 if (addr == NULL) {
8067 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8068 return EINVAL;
8069 }
8070 switch (addr->sa_family) {
8071#ifdef INET
8072 case AF_INET:
8073#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8074 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
8075 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8076 return (EINVAL);
8077 }
8078#endif
8079 break;
8080#endif
8081#ifdef INET6
8082 case AF_INET6:
8083#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8084 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
8085 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8086 return (EINVAL);
8087 }
8088#endif
8089 break;
8090#endif
8091 case AF_CONN:
8092#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8093 if (addr->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn)) {
8094 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8095 return (EINVAL);
8096 }
8097#endif
8098 break;
8099 default:
8100 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EAFNOSUPPORT);
8101 return (EAFNOSUPPORT);
8102 }
8103 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
8104 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK(inp);
8105 create_lock_on = 1;
8106
8107
8108 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
8109 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE)) {
8110 /* Should I really unlock ? */
8111 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EFAULT);
8112 error = EFAULT;
8113 goto out_now;
8114 }
8115#ifdef INET6
8116 if (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) &&
8117 (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6)) {
8118 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8119 error = EINVAL;
8120 goto out_now;
8121 }
8122#endif
8123 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) == SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
8124 /* Bind a ephemeral port */
8125 error = sctp_inpcb_bind(so, NULL, NULL, p);
8126 if (error) {
8127 goto out_now;
8128 }
8129 }
8130 /* Now do we connect? */
8131 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) &&
8132 (sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE))) {
8133 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8134 error = EINVAL;
8135 goto out_now;
8136 }
8137 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
8138 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED)) {
8139 /* We are already connected AND the TCP model */
8140 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EADDRINUSE);
8141 error = EADDRINUSE;
8142 goto out_now;
8143 }
8144 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) {
8145 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
8146 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
8147 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8148 } else {
8149 /* We increment here since sctp_findassociation_ep_addr() will
8150 * do a decrement if it finds the stcb as long as the locked
8151 * tcb (last argument) is NOT a TCB.. aka NULL.
8152 */
8153 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
8154 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, addr, NULL, NULL, NULL);
8155 if (stcb == NULL) {
8156 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
8157 } else {
8158 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8159 }
8160 }
8161 if (stcb != NULL) {
8162 /* Already have or am bring up an association */
8163 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EALREADY);
8164 error = EALREADY;
8165 goto out_now;
8166 }
8167
8168 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
8169#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
8170 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
8171 if (vrf_id == inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) {
8172 fnd = 1;
8173 break;
8174 }
8175 }
8176 if (!fnd) {
8177 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8178 error = EINVAL;
8179 goto out_now;
8180 }
8181#endif
8182 /* We are GOOD to go */
8183 stcb = sctp_aloc_assoc(inp, addr, &error, 0, vrf_id,
8184 inp->sctp_ep.pre_open_stream_count,
8185 inp->sctp_ep.port, p,
8186 SCTP_INITIALIZE_AUTH_PARAMS);
8187 if (stcb == NULL) {
8188 /* Gak! no memory */
8189 goto out_now;
8190 }
8191 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) {
8192 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
8193 /* Set the connected flag so we can queue data */
8194 soisconnecting(so);
8195 }
8196 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
8197 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&stcb->asoc.time_entered);
8198
8199 sctp_send_initiate(inp, stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
8200 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8201 out_now:
8202 if (create_lock_on) {
8203 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
8204 }
8205
8206 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
8207 return (error);
8208}
8209#endif
8210int
8211#if defined(__Userspace__)
8212sctp_listen(struct socket *so, int backlog, struct proc *p)
8213#elif defined(__FreeBSD__)
8214sctp_listen(struct socket *so, int backlog, struct thread *p)
8215#elif defined(_WIN32)
8216sctp_listen(struct socket *so, int backlog, PKTHREAD p)
8217#else
8218sctp_listen(struct socket *so, struct proc *p)
8219#endif
8220{
8221 /*
8222 * Note this module depends on the protocol processing being called
8223 * AFTER any socket level flags and backlog are applied to the
8224 * socket. The traditional way that the socket flags are applied is
8225 * AFTER protocol processing. We have made a change to the
8226 * sys/kern/uipc_socket.c module to reverse this but this MUST be in
8227 * place if the socket API for SCTP is to work properly.
8228 */
8229
8230 int error = 0;
8231 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8232
8233 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
8234 if (inp == NULL) {
8235 /* I made the same as TCP since we are not setup? */
8236 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8237 return (ECONNRESET);
8238 }
8239 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) {
8240 /* See if we have a listener */
8241 struct sctp_inpcb *tinp;
8242 union sctp_sockstore store;
8243
8244 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) == 0) {
8245 /* not bound all */
8246 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
8247
8248 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
8249 memcpy(&store, &laddr->ifa->address, sizeof(store));
8250 switch (store.sa.sa_family) {
8251#ifdef INET
8252 case AF_INET:
8253 store.sin.sin_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8254 break;
8255#endif
8256#ifdef INET6
8257 case AF_INET6:
8258 store.sin6.sin6_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8259 break;
8260#endif
8261#if defined(__Userspace__)
8262 case AF_CONN:
8263 store.sconn.sconn_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8264 break;
8265#endif
8266 default:
8267 break;
8268 }
8269 tinp = sctp_pcb_findep(&store.sa, 0, 0, inp->def_vrf_id);
8270 if (tinp && (tinp != inp) &&
8271 ((tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) == 0) &&
8272 ((tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) == 0) &&
8273 (SCTP_IS_LISTENING(tinp))) {
8274 /* we have a listener already and its not this inp. */
8275 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(tinp);
8276 return (EADDRINUSE);
8277 } else if (tinp) {
8278 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(tinp);
8279 }
8280 }
8281 } else {
8282 /* Setup a local addr bound all */
8283 memset(&store, 0, sizeof(store));
8284#ifdef INET6
8285 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
8286 store.sa.sa_family = AF_INET6;
8287#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8288 store.sa.sa_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
8289#endif
8290 }
8291#endif
8292#if defined(__Userspace__)
8293 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) {
8294 store.sa.sa_family = AF_CONN;
8295#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8296 store.sa.sa_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
8297#endif
8298 }
8299#endif
8300#ifdef INET
8301#if defined(__Userspace__)
8302 if (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) &&
8303 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) == 0)) {
8304#else
8305 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) {
8306#endif
8307 store.sa.sa_family = AF_INET;
8308#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
8309 store.sa.sa_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
8310#endif
8311 }
8312#endif
8313 switch (store.sa.sa_family) {
8314#ifdef INET
8315 case AF_INET:
8316 store.sin.sin_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8317 break;
8318#endif
8319#ifdef INET6
8320 case AF_INET6:
8321 store.sin6.sin6_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8322 break;
8323#endif
8324#if defined(__Userspace__)
8325 case AF_CONN:
8326 store.sconn.sconn_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8327 break;
8328#endif
8329 default:
8330 break;
8331 }
8332 tinp = sctp_pcb_findep(&store.sa, 0, 0, inp->def_vrf_id);
8333 if (tinp && (tinp != inp) &&
8334 ((tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) == 0) &&
8335 ((tinp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) == 0) &&
8336 (SCTP_IS_LISTENING(tinp))) {
8337 /* we have a listener already and its not this inp. */
8338 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(tinp);
8339 return (EADDRINUSE);
8340 } else if (tinp) {
8341 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(tinp);
8342 }
8343 }
8344 }
8345 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
8346#ifdef SCTP_LOCK_LOGGING
8347 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOCK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
8348 sctp_log_lock(inp, (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL, SCTP_LOG_LOCK_SOCK);
8349 }
8350#endif
8351#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
8352 SOCK_LOCK(so);
8353 error = solisten_proto_check(so);
8354 SOCK_UNLOCK(so);
8355 if (error) {
8356 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8357 return (error);
8358 }
8359#endif
8360 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PORTREUSE)) &&
8361 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
8362 /* The unlucky case
8363 * - We are in the tcp pool with this guy.
8364 * - Someone else is in the main inp slot.
8365 * - We must move this guy (the listener) to the main slot
8366 * - We must then move the guy that was listener to the TCP Pool.
8367 */
8368 if (sctp_swap_inpcb_for_listen(inp)) {
8369 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8370 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EADDRINUSE);
8371 return (EADDRINUSE);
8372 }
8373 }
8374
8375 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
8376 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED)) {
8377 /* We are already connected AND the TCP model */
8378 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8379 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EADDRINUSE);
8380 return (EADDRINUSE);
8381 }
8382 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8383 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
8384 /* We must do a bind. */
8385 if ((error = sctp_inpcb_bind(so, NULL, NULL, p))) {
8386 /* bind error, probably perm */
8387 return (error);
8388 }
8389 }
8390 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
8391#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8392 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) == 0) {
8393 SOCK_LOCK(so);
8394 solisten_proto(so, backlog);
8395 SOCK_UNLOCK(so);
8396 }
8397#elif defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__)
8398 SOCK_LOCK(so);
8399 solisten_proto(so, backlog);
8400#endif
8401#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
8402 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) {
8403 /* remove the ACCEPTCONN flag for one-to-many sockets */
8404#if defined(__Userspace__)
8405 so->so_options &= ~SCTP_SO_ACCEPTCONN;
8406#else
8407 so->so_options &= ~SO_ACCEPTCONN;
8408#endif
8409 }
8410 SOCK_UNLOCK(so);
8411#endif
8412#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__)
8413 if (backlog > 0) {
8414 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ACCEPTING;
8415 } else {
8416 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ACCEPTING;
8417 }
8418#else
8419 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ACCEPTING;
8420#endif
8421 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8422 return (error);
8423}
8424
8425static int sctp_defered_wakeup_cnt = 0;
8426
8427int
8428sctp_accept(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr **addr)
8429{
8430 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
8431 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8432 union sctp_sockstore store;
8433#ifdef INET6
8434#if defined(SCTP_KAME) && defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
8435 int error;
8436#endif
8437#endif
8438 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
8439
8440 if (inp == NULL) {
8441 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8442 return (ECONNRESET);
8443 }
8444 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
8445 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) {
8446 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8447 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EOPNOTSUPP);
8448 return (EOPNOTSUPP);
8449 }
8450 if (so->so_state & SS_ISDISCONNECTED) {
8451 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8452 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ECONNABORTED);
8453 return (ECONNABORTED);
8454 }
8455 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
8456 if (stcb == NULL) {
8457 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8458 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8459 return (ECONNRESET);
8460 }
8461 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
8462 store = stcb->asoc.primary_destination->ro._l_addr;
8463 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
8464 /* Wake any delayed sleep action */
8465 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONT_WAKE) {
8466 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONT_WAKE;
8467 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEOUTPUT) {
8468 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEOUTPUT;
8469 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&inp->sctp_socket->so_snd);
8470 if (sowriteable(inp->sctp_socket)) {
8471#if defined(__Userspace__)
8472 /*__Userspace__ calling sowwakup_locked because of SOCKBUF_LOCK above. */
8473#endif
8474#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__)
8475 sowwakeup_locked(inp->sctp_socket);
8476#else
8477#if defined(__APPLE__)
8478 /* socket is locked */
8479#endif
8480 sowwakeup(inp->sctp_socket);
8481#endif
8482 } else {
8483 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&inp->sctp_socket->so_snd);
8484 }
8485 }
8486 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEINPUT) {
8487 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAKEINPUT;
8488 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&inp->sctp_socket->so_rcv);
8489 if (soreadable(inp->sctp_socket)) {
8490 sctp_defered_wakeup_cnt++;
8491#if defined(__Userspace__)
8492 /*__Userspace__ calling sorwakup_locked because of SOCKBUF_LOCK above */
8493#endif
8494#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__)
8495 sorwakeup_locked(inp->sctp_socket);
8496#else
8497#if defined(__APPLE__)
8498 /* socket is locked */
8499#endif
8500 sorwakeup(inp->sctp_socket);
8501#endif
8502 } else {
8503 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&inp->sctp_socket->so_rcv);
8504 }
8505 }
8506 }
8507 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8508 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
8509 sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
8510 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ + SCTP_LOC_19);
8511 } else {
8512 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8513 }
8514 switch (store.sa.sa_family) {
8515#ifdef INET
8516 case AF_INET:
8517 {
8518 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
8519
8520 SCTP_MALLOC_SONAME(sin, struct sockaddr_in *, sizeof *sin);
8521 if (sin == NULL)
8522 return (ENOMEM);
8523 sin->sin_family = AF_INET;
8524#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
8525 sin->sin_len = sizeof(*sin);
8526#endif
8527 sin->sin_port = store.sin.sin_port;
8528 sin->sin_addr = store.sin.sin_addr;
8529 *addr = (struct sockaddr *)sin;
8530 break;
8531 }
8532#endif
8533#ifdef INET6
8534 case AF_INET6:
8535 {
8536 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
8537
8538 SCTP_MALLOC_SONAME(sin6, struct sockaddr_in6 *, sizeof *sin6);
8539 if (sin6 == NULL)
8540 return (ENOMEM);
8541 sin6->sin6_family = AF_INET6;
8542#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
8543 sin6->sin6_len = sizeof(*sin6);
8544#endif
8545 sin6->sin6_port = store.sin6.sin6_port;
8546 sin6->sin6_addr = store.sin6.sin6_addr;
8547#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
8548#ifdef SCTP_KAME
8549 if ((error = sa6_recoverscope(sin6)) != 0) {
8550 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin6);
8551 return (error);
8552 }
8553#else
8554 if (IN6_IS_SCOPE_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr))
8555 /*
8556 * sin6->sin6_scope_id =
8557 * ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[1]);
8558 */
8559 in6_recoverscope(sin6, &sin6->sin6_addr, NULL); /* skip ifp check */
8560 else
8561 sin6->sin6_scope_id = 0; /* XXX */
8562#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
8563#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
8564 *addr = (struct sockaddr *)sin6;
8565 break;
8566 }
8567#endif
8568#if defined(__Userspace__)
8569 case AF_CONN:
8570 {
8571 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
8572
8573 SCTP_MALLOC_SONAME(sconn, struct sockaddr_conn *, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
8574 if (sconn == NULL) {
8575 return (ENOMEM);
8576 }
8577 sconn->sconn_family = AF_CONN;
8578#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
8579 sconn->sconn_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
8580#endif
8581 sconn->sconn_port = store.sconn.sconn_port;
8582 sconn->sconn_addr = store.sconn.sconn_addr;
8583 *addr = (struct sockaddr *)sconn;
8584 break;
8585 }
8586#endif
8587 default:
8588 /* TSNH */
8589 break;
8590 }
8591 return (0);
8592}
8593
8594#ifdef INET
8595int
8596#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8597sctp_ingetaddr(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr **addr)
8598{
8599 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
8600#else
8601sctp_ingetaddr(struct socket *so, struct mbuf *nam)
8602{
8603 struct sockaddr_in *sin = mtod(nam, struct sockaddr_in *);
8604#endif
8605 uint32_t vrf_id;
8606 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8607 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifa;
8608
8609 /*
8610 * Do the malloc first in case it blocks.
8611 */
8612#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8613 SCTP_MALLOC_SONAME(sin, struct sockaddr_in *, sizeof *sin);
8614 if (sin == NULL)
8615 return (ENOMEM);
8616#else
8617 SCTP_BUF_LEN(nam) = sizeof(*sin);
8618 memset(sin, 0, sizeof(*sin));
8619#endif
8620 sin->sin_family = AF_INET;
8621#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
8622 sin->sin_len = sizeof(*sin);
8623#endif
8624 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
8625 if (!inp) {
8626#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8627 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin);
8628#endif
8629 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8630 return (ECONNRESET);
8631 }
8632 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
8633 sin->sin_port = inp->sctp_lport;
8634 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
8635 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) {
8636 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
8637 struct sockaddr_in *sin_a;
8638 struct sctp_nets *net;
8639 int fnd;
8640
8641 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
8642 if (stcb == NULL) {
8643 goto notConn;
8644 }
8645 fnd = 0;
8646 sin_a = NULL;
8647 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
8648 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
8649 sin_a = (struct sockaddr_in *)&net->ro._l_addr;
8650 if (sin_a == NULL)
8651 /* this will make coverity happy */
8652 continue;
8653
8654 if (sin_a->sin_family == AF_INET) {
8655 fnd = 1;
8656 break;
8657 }
8658 }
8659 if ((!fnd) || (sin_a == NULL)) {
8660 /* punt */
8661 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8662 goto notConn;
8663 }
8664
8665 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
8666 sctp_ifa = sctp_source_address_selection(inp,
8667 stcb,
8668 (sctp_route_t *)&net->ro,
8669 net, 0, vrf_id);
8670 if (sctp_ifa) {
8671 sin->sin_addr = sctp_ifa->address.sin.sin_addr;
8672 sctp_free_ifa(sctp_ifa);
8673 }
8674 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8675 } else {
8676 /* For the bound all case you get back 0 */
8677 notConn:
8678 sin->sin_addr.s_addr = 0;
8679 }
8680
8681 } else {
8682 /* Take the first IPv4 address in the list */
8683 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
8684 int fnd = 0;
8685
8686 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
8687 if (laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family == AF_INET) {
8688 struct sockaddr_in *sin_a;
8689
8690 sin_a = &laddr->ifa->address.sin;
8691 sin->sin_addr = sin_a->sin_addr;
8692 fnd = 1;
8693 break;
8694 }
8695 }
8696 if (!fnd) {
8697#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8698 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin);
8699#endif
8700 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8701 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOENT);
8702 return (ENOENT);
8703 }
8704 }
8705 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8706#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8707 (*addr) = (struct sockaddr *)sin;
8708#endif
8709 return (0);
8710}
8711
8712int
8713#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8714sctp_peeraddr(struct socket *so, struct sockaddr **addr)
8715{
8716 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
8717#else
8718sctp_peeraddr(struct socket *so, struct mbuf *nam)
8719{
8720 struct sockaddr_in *sin = mtod(nam, struct sockaddr_in *);
8721
8722#endif
8723 int fnd;
8724 struct sockaddr_in *sin_a;
8725 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8726 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
8727 struct sctp_nets *net;
8728
8729 /* Do the malloc first in case it blocks. */
8730#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8731 SCTP_MALLOC_SONAME(sin, struct sockaddr_in *, sizeof *sin);
8732 if (sin == NULL)
8733 return (ENOMEM);
8734#else
8735 SCTP_BUF_LEN(nam) = sizeof(*sin);
8736 memset(sin, 0, sizeof(*sin));
8737#endif
8738 sin->sin_family = AF_INET;
8739#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
8740 sin->sin_len = sizeof(*sin);
8741#endif
8742
8743 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
8744 if ((inp == NULL) ||
8745 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) == 0)) {
8746 /* UDP type and listeners will drop out here */
8747#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8748 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin);
8749#endif
8750 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOTCONN);
8751 return (ENOTCONN);
8752 }
8753 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
8754 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
8755 if (stcb) {
8756 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
8757 }
8758 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
8759 if (stcb == NULL) {
8760#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8761 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin);
8762#endif
8763 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, EINVAL);
8764 return (ECONNRESET);
8765 }
8766 fnd = 0;
8767 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
8768 sin_a = (struct sockaddr_in *)&net->ro._l_addr;
8769 if (sin_a->sin_family == AF_INET) {
8770 fnd = 1;
8771 sin->sin_port = stcb->rport;
8772 sin->sin_addr = sin_a->sin_addr;
8773 break;
8774 }
8775 }
8776 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8777 if (!fnd) {
8778 /* No IPv4 address */
8779#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8780 SCTP_FREE_SONAME(sin);
8781#endif
8782 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_USRREQ, ENOENT);
8783 return (ENOENT);
8784 }
8785#if !defined(__Userspace__)
8786 (*addr) = (struct sockaddr *)sin;
8787#endif
8788 return (0);
8789}
